<br>
First - there are 8 (or seven with one split in two pieces) levels to this dungeon<br>
<br>
They are all in the same zone, but can only be reached via Teleports which are built into the dungeon.<br>
<br>
The dungeon is great - I've fought extensively on levels 1 and 2 and have keys (on Thrar) to levels 2 and 3<br>
<br>
Some notes on access and motif:<br>
<br>
The dungeon was built by an evil necromancer who fabricated it out of the solidified souls - hence the &quot;frozen shadow&quot;.  The first levels of the dungeon are predominantly undead.<br>
<br>
The tower is located on the &quot;middle&quot; island in Iceclad - there are scads of islands -but of the three largest it is in the middle (biggest connecting to Eastern Wastes via the Dragon Bridge and also has the dragon portal, middle having ToFS and the &quot;friendly&quot; gnoll camp - and Lodizal, smallest having the gnome pirate igloos and the Icebreaker dock).<br>
<br>
The tower is surrounded by Shadowed Guardians which are Snow Dervishes on steroids.  To enter - you run up and look for the shimmering portal on the side and click on the portal.  Unless you are invis, the guardians will whack on you a bit - don't dally.<br>
<br>
The first level is relatively small and has some good drops but not many.  There is a placeholder spawn for a named undead gnoll (the LUG - Large Undead Gnoll) who drops the key to level 2.<br>
<br>
Access to any level other than one requires a key.  The keys are used on mirrors on the wall.  Hold the key - click on the mirror and whoosh - you are at the portal in location of the new level.  The keys teleport the whole party - or atleast everyone within range of the teleportation.<br>
<br>
Levels 2-8 (or 2-7(A/B)) have two exits - one is the portal to the next level up, the second is the portal out.  The portals out are frequently hidden behind secret doors.  To advance to the next level, you have to spawn the keyholder.  The keyholder on Level 2 is immediately after you kill a wandering placeholder.   Getting her to spawn is tough as the PH wanders so you kind of have to scrounge the level and the level is quite large and quite dangerous.<br>
<br>
Now, a quick note on exiting - you really need to invis (not invis to undead but invis) everyone up.  Exit the dungeon mirror portals do not require keys and drop you out right at the shimmering portal surrounded by Shadowed Guardians.  If you aren't invis - you could very well end up dead.<br>
<br>
The people in the guild who I know have fought here are myself, Lyri, Adlehardt, Tarrian, Ishlyn.  Key access is very, very important.  If you have a party wipeout - you could very well end up in a situation where you can't get back to your bodies.  So there are several options:<br>
<br>
(1) have a porting caster bind at a safe spot in Iceclad and make sure they port out of the dungeon when the wipeout starts<br>
(2) have monk with key <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    The monk would FD when the wipeout starts and still be in position to get a cleric in.<br>
(3) leave a key (or set of keys) on a dueled corpse out in Iceclad in a safe spot.  Leave keys on the body until they are needed for a CR - loot keys when raid ends.<br>
<br>
I would be interested in leading or helping to lead this type of thing, but good group balance is critical in ToFS.  I know Tarrian and Lyri were trying to get up an event here a while back, I'd like to work with them if they are willing.<br>
<br>
Regardless, this cannot be a &quot;pickup&quot; event - we've got to assure that certain classes are present - Invis to Undead and Invisibility or evac are critical for safe entrance and exit from the dungeon.  We've also got to assure that we've got enough keys.<br>
<br>
